§ RENDERGRAPH (v1, not-deferred)
  type RenderGraph : compile-time-DAG {
    nodes : [Pass ; N]
    edges : [(Handle<Pass>, Handle<Pass>) ; M]
  }
  @staged-expansion : DAG → flat-cmdbuf-sequence
  compile-time analysis :
    barrier-insertion (RAW/WAR/WAW automatic)
    resource-aliasing (transient-texture memory-reuse)
    async-queue-scheduling (compute + graphics overlap)
    telemetry-probe insertion per-pass (R18)
  ≡ eliminates entire class of validation-layer-errors

§ ENGINE-SEMANTIC-ERRORS → compile-time-caught
  ✓ SDF without Lipschitz-bound → "cannot ray-march : no L-tag"
  ✓ GPU-struct std140 vs std430 mismatch → "layout incompatible"
  ✓ CmdBuf-leak (no end_frame) → "linear resource unconsumed"
  ✓ Stale-Handle deref → runtime-panic with captured-context
  ✓ audio-callback with Alloc-ancestor → "NoAlloc violation in callback"
  ✓ shader runtime-if over scene-shape → warned "use @staged"
  ✓ non-@differentiable call inside @differentiable → compile-error
  ✓ RenderGraph cycle → compile-error pre-expansion
  ✓ VoxelVolume simultaneous mut-ref + render → iso-violation
  ✓ {Power<budget>} breach in profile → CI-fail (R18+§§ 23)

∎ ENGINE
